FuncDef: The reset igmp snooping qinq-group command deletes multicast entries on dot1q termination sub-interfaces. The reset igmp snooping qinq-group command deletes multicast entries on dot1q termination sub-interfaces.
CLIs: reset igmp snooping qinq-group { all | interface { <interface-type> <interface-number> | <interface-name> } [ pe-vid <pe-vid> [ <group-address> [ mask { <group-mask> | <mask-length> } ] [ <source-address> [ mask { <source-mask> | <source-mask-length> } ] ] ] ] }

ParaDef.Info:
Deletes multicast entries on all QinQ or dot1q termination sub-interfaces.
-

Deletes multicast entries on a specified QinQ or dot1q termination sub-interface.
-

Specifies the type and number of an interface.
-

Specifies the ID of the VLAN to which a PE belongs.
For the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6860-SAN, CE6866K, CE6866, CE6860-HAM, CE6855-48XS8CQ, CE6885-SAN, CE8850-SAN, CE8855, CE8851-32CQ4BQ, CE8851K, CE8851-32CQ8DQ-P, CE8850-HAM, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K, CE6820S, CE6885, CE6885-T, CE6885-LL (standard forwarding mode) and CE6863E-48S8CQ:The value is an integer ranging from 1 to 4094.
For the CE6885-LL (low latency mode):The value is an integer ranging from 1 to 1023.

Specifies a multicast group address.
This value is in dotted decimal notation.

Specifies the mask of a multicast group address.
This value is in dotted decimal notation.

Specifies the mask length of a multicast group address.
The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 32.

Specifies a multicast source address.
This value is in dotted decimal notation.

Specifies the mask of a multicast source address.
This value is in dotted decimal notation.

Specifies the mask length of a multicast source address.
The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 32.
